#!/bin/sh

cd ~/faststorage/ClaudiaI/Pasha_Results/unscaled_wigs

computeMatrix scale-regions \
-R "/home/schmidm/annotations/hg19/RefSeqGRCh37.3/Refseq_single_isoform_pc_genes_allquintiles.bed" \
-S *_[P,I][o,n]*.bw \
--upstream=2000 --downstream=5000 \
--averageTypeBins=mean --missingDataAsZero --binSize=50 \
--outFileName deeptools_out/Refseqv3_single_isoform_pc_gene_allq_scaleregions_matrix.gz \
--numberOfProcessors 4

echo "done"

bin_values

add an x-axis value

for plotting of data with upstream body and downstream regions.

(bin_values %<>%
  separate(rel_pos, c('anchor', 'rel_pos'), sep=' ') %>%
  mutate(rel_pos = ifelse(is.na(rel_pos), 0, as.integer(rel_pos))))
x_bins <- distinct(bin_values, anchor, rel_pos)

(upstream <- filter(x_bins, anchor == 'TSS') %$% rel_pos %>% min)

(body_min <- filter(x_bins, anchor == 'body') %$% rel_pos %>% min)
(body <- filter(x_bins, anchor == 'body') %$% rel_pos %>% max)

(TESmin <- filter(x_bins, anchor == 'TES') %$% rel_pos %>% min)
(TESmax <- filter(x_bins, anchor == 'TES') %$% rel_pos %>% max)
(bin_values %<>%
  mutate(x_value = case_when(.$anchor == 'TSS' ~ .$rel_pos - upstream + body_min,
                             .$anchor == 'body' ~ .$rel_pos - upstream + body_min,
                             .$anchor == 'TES' ~ .$rel_pos - upstream  + body_min + body + body_min)))

metagene profiles raw unscaled values

bin_values_metagene <- bin_values %>%
  filter(x_value >= 1500, x_value <= 4000) %>%
  group_by(siRNA, run, main_run, ab, anchor, rel_pos, x_value, quintile) %>%
  summarize(mean_value = mean(value))
lineplot_theme_scaleregions <- list(lineplot_theme,
  geom_vline(xintercept=c(2000, 3000), linetype=3),
  scale_x_continuous(limits=c(1500, 4000),
                     breaks = c(1500,2000,3000,4000), 
                     labels = c('-500bp', 'TSS', 'TES', '+1kb')))
raw_plot <- function(tbl) {
  ggplot(tbl) +
  geom_line(aes(x=x_value, y=mean_value, color=siRNA), alpha=.7) +
  facet_grid(quintile ~ ab + run) +
  lineplot_theme_scaleregions +
  ylab('raw counts')
}
bin_values_metagene %>%
  filter(!is.na(quintile)) %>%
  raw_plot

bin_values_metagene %>%
  filter(quintile == 5) %>%
  raw_plot

bin_values_metagene %>%
  filter(quintile == 1) %>%
  raw_plot

bin_values_metagene %>%
  filter(main_run == 'CI siARS2', quintile == 1) %>%
  raw_plot +
  ylim(-2,30)

bin_values_metagene %>%
  filter(main_run == 'CI siARS2', quintile == 5) %>%
  raw_plot +
  ylim(-.2,3)

bin_values_metagene %>%
  group_by(quintile, ab, siRNA, main_run, x_value) %>%
  mutate(upper = max(mean_value), lower = min(mean_value), center = mean(mean_value)) %>%
ggplot(.) +
  geom_line(aes(x=x_value, y=mean_value, color=siRNA), alpha=.7) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(x=x_value, ymin=lower, ymax=upper, fill=siRNA), alpha=.7 ) +
  facet_grid(quintile~ab+main_run) +
  lineplot_theme_scaleregions +
  ylab('raw counts')

BGsub

BGsub and scaling is normally part of the arsRtools::scale_chip_matrix function. Here the individual code parts are shown:
Note though that quintiles are normally not relevant and dropped in the scale_chip_matrix function.

first split inputs and ips

(inputs <- dplyr::filter(bin_values, ab=='Input') %>%
    dplyr::select(id, x_value, sample_name, value) %>%
    dplyr::rename(used_input = sample_name, Input = value))

Here we use Refseq_pc_g2k_q1_second_half_body_scales from package arsRtools for scaling

(BGsub <- left_join(ips, inputs) %>%
    dplyr::select(id, quintile, siRNA, ab, main_run, run, x_value, ChIP, Input) %>%
    left_join(., Refseq_pc_g2k_q1_second_half_body_scales) %>%
    mutate(scaled_input = Input*input_scale_factor,
           BGSub_ChIP = ChIP-scaled_input))

This will result in all ChIP samples having quintile 5 at an average value of ~ 0. This can be visualize in the metagene profiles for quintile 5:

BGsub_metagene <- BGsub %>%
  group_by(siRNA, run, main_run, x_value, quintile) %>%
  summarize(mean_BGSub_value = mean(BGSub_ChIP)) 
BGsub_plot <- function(tbl) {
  ggplot(tbl) +
  geom_line(aes(x=x_value, y=mean_BGSub_value, color=siRNA), alpha=.7) +
  facet_grid(quintile ~ run) +
  lineplot_theme_scaleregions +
  ylab('BGsub raw counts')
}
BGsub_metagene %>%
  filter(!is.na(quintile)) %>%
  BGsub_plot

p <- BGsub_metagene %>%
  filter(quintile == 5) %>%
  BGsub_plot

p + ylim(-100,100) + ylab('BGsub raw counts')

BGsub_metagene %>%
  filter(quintile == 1) %>%
  BGsub_plot

BGsub_metagene %>%
  filter(main_run == 'CI siARS2', quintile == 1) %>%
  BGsub_plot + 
  ylim(-2,30)

BGsub_metagene %>%
  filter(main_run == 'CI siARS2', quintile == 5) %>%
  BGsub_plot + 
  ylim(-.2,3)

scaling

Scaling tries to adjust the ChIP samples from different runs between each other. This is done using the gene body information from quintile 1. One can see the effect quite clearly on TSS-proximal metagene profiles for quintile 1..

(scaled_BGsub <- BGsub %>%
    mutate(scaled_BGSub_ChIP = BGSub_ChIP * chip_scale_factor,
           siRNA = factor(siRNA, levels=c('siARS2', 'siFFL', 'siRRP40', 'siZ18')),
           run = factor(run, levels=c('CI62', 'CI63',
                                      'MA72_z18', 'MA73_z18',
                                      'MA72_rrp40', 'MA73_rrp40')),
           main_run = factor(main_run, levels=c('CI siARS2',
                                                'MA siZ18',
                                                'MA siRRP40'))) %>%
    dplyr::select(id, quintile, main_run, run, siRNA, x_value, scaled_BGSub_ChIP))
